

	 
      have you ever closed your eyes and listened (?) to the thought patterns inside your brain? it seems like first, there is a voice saying a sentence or name of an object or whatever. next, nanoseconds later, you echo the phrase and identify the subject matter, forming a cognitive thought. after that, if you are talking, you say it out loud. that is the third step. sometimes ppl skip the second step and blurt out whatever it is. other times, ppl seem to get caught up in the second step and dwell on its meaning, without ever going to the final step...
    
